{
  "texts": [
    "The fixed determinant condition in G yields H = 0, and together with flatness of ∇ ad and (20a) we get that Ric | V×V = Ric h (under the correspondence from Proposition 2.12).",
    "Since all inner products on the orbit G • h ⊂ Sym 2 + (𝔫 *) define pairwise isometric, invariant Ricci soliton metrics on the fibres of π: M → B, we have a derivation field(22) D:= -h -1 Ric h -1 2 h ∈ Γ Der(adM).",
    "Lemma 3.2 yields a vertical X D ∈ Γ(T M) such that Ric g | V×V = (-1 2 g -1 2 L X D g)| V×V.Using (17b), we see that the horizontal part of equation ( 1) is satisfied thanks to minimality of the orbits and (20b).",
    "Finally, we claim that the mixed terms in Ric g vanish.",
    "To see that, given b ∈ B we may identify the fibre (adM) b with a metric Lie algebra (𝔫, h 0) whose Ricci endomorphism is 1 2 β."
  ]
